n          \"drug_or_class\",\r\n          \"reason\"\r\n        ],\r\n        \"properties\": {\r\n          \"drug_or_class\": {\r\n            \"type\": \"string\"\r\n          },\r\n          \"reason\": {\r\n            \"type\": \"string\"\r\n          }\r\n        }\r\n      }\r\n    },\r\n    \"follow_up\": {\r\n      \"type\": \"object\",\r\n      \"description\": \"��üƻ�\",\r\n      \"properties\": {\r\n        \"next_visit_days\": {\r\n          \"type\": \"number\"\r\n        },\r\n        \"red_flags\": {\r\n          \"type\": \"array\",\r\n          \"description\": \"��Ҫ���������Σ������\",\r\n          \"items\": {\r\n            \"type\": \"string\"\r\n          }\r\n        }\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n}","stderr":"\nShell cwd was reset to C:\\Users\\<USER>\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\his-cpoe-20260531-130330-5ZzDJ5","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-068b778e-74ac-9213-87b6-fdd1fa4f34e0","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"auto","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the key information. Let me analyze the patient case:\n\n**Patient Summary:**\n- 28-year-old male, 68kg, 175cm\n- No allergies\n- No comorbidities\n- No current medications\n- Pregnancy status: none\n- Renal function: normal (eGFR 105, CrCl 110)\n- Hepatic function: normal\n- Chief complaint: 咳嗽发热 3 天 (cough and fever for 3 days)\n- Present illness: 3 days ago after catching cold, developed cough with small amount of white sputum (no yellow purulent sputum); low fever (max 37.8°C), self-medicated with 板蓝根 without significant improvement; no shortness of breath, no hemoptysis.\n- Primary diagnosis: 急性上呼吸道感染 (Acute upper respiratory tract infection), ICD-10: J06.9\n- Vitals: T 37.6°C, BP 118/76, HR 84, RR 18, SpO2 98%\n- Physical exam: conscious, throat mildly congested without exudate, lung sounds normal, no wheezing, no pleural rub\n- Labs: WBC 7.8 (normal), N% 62% (normal), CRP 4.1 (normal), PCT 0.05 (normal)\n\n**Clinical Analysis:**\nThis is a 28-year-old healthy male with an acute upper respiratory infection. Key features:\n- Low-grade fever (37.8°C max, currently 37.6°C)\n- Cough with minimal white (non-purulent) sputum\n- Normal throat (mild congestion, no exudate)\n- Normal lung auscultation\n- All inflammatory markers normal (WBC, N%, CRP, PCT all within normal range)\n- No comorbidities, no allergies, normal organ function\n\nThis is most likely a **viral upper respiratory infection** (common cold / mild acute bronchitis). The normal inflammatory markers, white sputum, and low-grade fever all point to a viral etiology rather than bacterial.\n\n**Prescribing Decision:**\nFor a viral URI in a healthy adult:\n1. **No antibiotics needed** - Normal WBC/CRP/PCT, white sputum, mild fever all suggest viral infection. Antibiotics would be inappropriate.\n2. **Symptomatic treatment**:\n   - Cough: Right, the patient has a cough. I could consider a cough suppressant or expectorant. Given it's productive (white sputum), an expectorant might be more appropriate than a suppressant. But the sputum is minimal. Let me think...\n   - Actually, for a mild productive cough, I'd lean towards not suppressing it (cough serves to clear secretions). But if the cough is bothersome, a mild expectorant/antitussive could help. Common options in Chinese hospital settings:\n     - 右美沙芬 (dextromethorphan) - antitussive\n     - 愈创甘油醚 (guaifenesin) - expectorant\n     - 氨溴索 (ambroxol) - mucolytic/expectorant\n     - For a mild cough with minimal white sputum, 氨溴索 might be appropriate\n   - Fever: T 37.6°C is low-grade. The patient hasn't reached 38.5°C threshold for antipyretics being routinely recommended. But they're uncomfortable. PRN antipyretic might be appropriate.\n     - 对乙酰氨基酚 (acetaminophen/paracetamol) or 布洛芬 (ibuprofen) - PRN for fever >38.5°C or discomfort\n   - Sore throat: Mild congestion. Could use local treatment or systemic. Since it's mild, PRN approach.\n   \nLet me design the prescription:\n\n1. **氨溴索 (Ambroxol)** - mucolytic for the productive cough, helps thin and clear sputum. Common formulation: 30mg tablet, 30mg bid PO, 5-7 days.\n2. **对乙酰氨基酚 (Acetaminophen)** - PRN for fever/discomfort. 0.5g tablet, prn PO when T>38.5°C or significant discomfort.\n\nWait, let me reconsider. The fever is only 37.6°C and the patient already tried 板蓝根 (a Chinese herbal cold remedy). The cough is the main complaint with minimal white sputum.\n\nActually, let me reconsider whether antipyretics are needed at all. 37.6°C is not high enough to warrant routine antipyretic use. A PRN order for when fever exceeds 38.5°C would be reasonable though.\n\nFor the cough:\n- 氨溴索 (ambroxol) is a reasonable choice for productive cough - it's a mucolytic that helps thin mucus. Common dose: 30mg bid or tid PO, 5-7 days.\n\nLet me also look up these drugs to get their specifications and NRDL info.\n\nActually, I should look up the drugs via the API before prescribing. Let me do that.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"989e347e-3361-4bc8-ba0e-d6a750171bd2","session_id":"08d5d227-1723-461b-94bd-7dea71b3309e"}
